Session 21: Android Architecture, Security Model & Rooting
üîπ BASIC MCQs (10)
1. Android is an operating system primarily designed for:
A. Servers
B. Desktop computers
C. Mobile devices
D. Supercomputers

2. Android architecture is based on:
A. Monolithic kernel
B. Microkernel
C. Linux kernel
D. Windows kernel

3. Which layer of Android directly interacts with hardware?
A. Application layer
B. Application Framework
C. Linux Kernel
D. Libraries

4. Android applications are primarily written in:
A. C only
B. Java / Kotlin
C. Python
D. Assembly

5. APK stands for:
A. Android Package
B. Application Program Kernel
C. Android Package Kit
D. Application Package Key

6. Android file system is mainly based on:
A. NTFS
B. FAT32
C. Linux file system
D. exFAT

7. Which directory stores application data in Android?
A. /system
B. /boot
C. /data
D. /cache

8. Android Security Model mainly relies on:
A. Password only
B. Application sandboxing
C. Antivirus
D. Firewall

9. Device rooting means:
A. Installing apps
B. Gaining privileged (root) access
C. Encrypting device
D. Updating OS

10. Android Emulator is used to:
A. Root devices
B. Simulate Android devices on PC
C. Crack apps
D. Modify kernel

üî∏ INTERMEDIATE MCQs (10)
11. Android architecture consists of how many major layers?
A. Two
B. Three
C. Four
D. Five

12. Which Android layer provides system services like Activity Manager?
A. Applications
B. Application Framework
C. Libraries
D. Linux Kernel

13. Android build process generates which final output?
A. .exe
B. .apk
C. .jar
D. .bin

14. Android app components include:
A. Activities, Services, Broadcast Receivers, Content Providers
B. Kernel modules only
C. DLL files
D. Network drivers

15. Each Android app runs with:
A. Same user ID
B. Root privileges
C. Unique user ID
D. Admin privileges

16. Android permission system helps in:
A. Improving UI
B. Restricting app access to resources
C. Speeding execution
D. Rooting device

17. Rooting an Android device disables:
A. Internet
B. Application sandboxing protection
C. Display drivers
D. Emulator

18. Which file contains Android app permissions?
A. build.gradle
B. AndroidManifest.xml
C. classes.dex
D. resources.arsc

19. Rooted devices are MORE vulnerable because they:
A. Are faster
B. Bypass OS security controls
C. Use encryption
D. Are updated

20. Android Emulator is preferred in labs because it:
A. Is faster than real device
B. Avoids risk to physical device
C. Needs root
D. Is insecure

